<body>
Reports comparisons with NULL that can be replaced with IS NULL or IS NOT NULL operators.
<p>Example (Microsoft SQL Server):</p>
<pre><code>CREATE TABLE foo ( id int );

SELECT * FROM foo WHERE NULL = NULL;
SELECT * FROM foo WHERE NULL != NULL;</code></pre>
<p>The <code>NULL = NULL</code> can be replaced with <code>IS NULL</code>, the <code>NULL != NULL</code> comparison
  with <code>IS NOT NULL</code>. To do this replacement, you can use <b>Use IS NULL operator</b> or <b>Use IS NOT NULL operator</b>
  quick-fixes.</p>
<pre><code>SELECT * FROM foo WHERE NULL IS NULL;
SELECT * FROM foo WHERE NULL IS NOT NULL;</code></pre>
</body>
